If not ready, it selects more tiles under the byte budget, issues prefetches with use-by times, and cancels any fetch whose predicted ETA > use-by.

After commit, late tiles can apply deterministic refinement (versioned, idempotent).

Training path (must-complete)

Training identifies the required tiles for exact gradients and required optimizer-state tiles.

It prioritizes fetching these tiles to satisfy a must-complete window before backward/sync (no ‚Äúcommit early‚Äù rule).

If required tiles aren‚Äôt ready, it continues fetching/reprioritizing until they are.

Once ready, it runs backward + sync, performs optimizer update, writes back updated tiles/state with a version bump, and ends the step.

Short PPT summary (2 lines)

Inference: Commit-by-deadline using quality gates (stability/error), fetching only high-value tiles with use-by cancellation to bound tail latency.
Training: Must-complete mode guarantees exact gradients by ensuring required weight/optimizer tiles arrive before backward/sync, then updates and writes back versioned tiles.
